answerText: De Profundis[10] This author of De Profundis is better known for writing The Picture of Dorian Gray and The Importance of Being Earnest.

question: Question:  [10] Name this letter, which names Jesus as a forerunner to the romantic movement. It was written by a man who was jailed after suing the Marquess of Queensberry for libel.
